l2tpv3.name: l2tpv3
l2tpv3.contactinfo: Layer Two Tunneling Protocol Extensions WG Working Group Area: Internet Working Group Name: l2tpext General Discussion: l2tp@l2tp.net
l2tpv3.description: The MIB module that describes managed objects of general use by the Layer Two Tunneling Protocol, Version 3 (L2TPv3).

L2tpv3MilliSeconds.name: L2tpv3MilliSeconds
L2tpv3MilliSeconds.description: A period of time, measured in units of .001 seconds. When used in conjunction with the DISPLAY-HINT, shows seconds and fractions of a second with a resolution of .001 of a second.

L2tpv3TransportType.name: L2tpv3TransportType
L2tpv3TransportType.description: Supported L2TP transport types. Different transports may define MIB extensions to the L2TP control connection table to fully describe the transport layer. Objects of this type may be used to determine which MIB extensions to reference.

L2tpv3DataSequencing.name: L2tpv3DataSequencing
L2tpv3DataSequencing.description: L2TP data sequencing levels. A value of 'none' indicates that no received data packets require sequencing. A value of 'nonIP' indicates that only non-IP data packets require sequencing. A value of 'all' indicates that all received data packets require sequencing. The appropriate sequencing level is communicated to the peer via the Data Sequencing AVP.

l2tpv3StackCfgAdminState.name: l2tpv3StackCfgAdminState
l2tpv3StackCfgAdminState.description: The administrative state of the L2TP stack. Setting this object to 'disabled' causes all control connections to be immediately disconnected. After this point, no further control connections or session may be initiated or accepted. The value of this object must be maintained in non-volatile memory.

l2tpv3StackCfgDrain.name: l2tpv3StackCfgDrain
l2tpv3StackCfgDrain.description: Setting this object to 'true' prevents any new control connections and/or sessions from being initiated or accepted. However, it does not disconnect any active control connections and/or sessions. The 'l2tpv3StackStatsIsDraining' object and the 'l2tpv3CtrlStatsIsDraining' object of each control connection is set to 'true'. To cancel a drain, this object is set to 'false'. The value of this object must be maintained in non-volatile memory.

l2tpv3StackStatsVersion.name: l2tpv3StackStatsVersion
l2tpv3StackStatsVersion.description: The highest protocol version number supported by this L2TP stack.

l2tpv3StackStatsRevision.name: l2tpv3StackStatsRevision
l2tpv3StackStatsRevision.description: The revision number of the L2TP stack.

l2tpv3StackStatsVendorName.name: l2tpv3StackStatsVendorName
l2tpv3StackStatsVendorName.description: The vendor name of the L2TP stack.

l2tpv3StackStatsAdminState.name: l2tpv3StackStatsAdminState
l2tpv3StackStatsAdminState.description: The administrative state of the L2TP stack. It reflects the value of the l2tpv3StackCfgAdminState object.

l2tpv3StackStatsIsDraining.name: l2tpv3StackStatsIsDraining
l2tpv3StackStatsIsDraining.description: Indicates whether the L2TP stack is draining sessions from all control connections.

l2tpv3StackStatsNumCtrlEst.name: l2tpv3StackStatsNumCtrlEst
l2tpv3StackStatsNumCtrlEst.description: The total number of control connections that are currently established.

l2tpv3StackStatsNumSessEst.name: l2tpv3StackStatsNumSessEst
l2tpv3StackStatsNumSessEst.description: The total number of sessions that are currently established.

l2tpv3CtrlCfgTable.name: l2tpv3CtrlCfgTable
l2tpv3CtrlCfgTable.description: Table used to (re)configure the operational characteristics of a single L2TP control connection. There is a 1:1 correspondence between conceptual rows of this table and conceptual rows of the l2tpv3CtrlStatsTable. Entries in this table have the same persistency characteristics as that of the l2tpv3CtrlStatsTable.

l2tpv3CtrlCfgEntry.name: l2tpv3CtrlCfgEntry
l2tpv3CtrlCfgEntry.description: An L2TP control connection configuration entry. Entries in this table are added and deleted as a result of protocol interactions or management operations. The latter occurs when a row is instantiated in the l2tpv3CtrlCfgTable row and the encapsulation method is 'l2tp'.

l2tpv3CtrlCfgIfIndex.name: l2tpv3CtrlCfgIfIndex
l2tpv3CtrlCfgIfIndex.description: Value equal to the ifIndex value of the Interfaces Group MIB for an interface of type L2TP.

l2tpv3CtrlCfgRouterID.name: l2tpv3CtrlCfgRouterID
l2tpv3CtrlCfgRouterID.description: The local router ID of this peer, as communicated via the Router ID AVP for this control connection.

l2tpv3CtrlCfgTransport.name: l2tpv3CtrlCfgTransport
l2tpv3CtrlCfgTransport.description: The transport type of this control connection entry. This object cannot be modified when the control connection is in a connecting or connected state.

l2tpv3CtrlCfgPWCap.name: l2tpv3CtrlCfgPWCap
l2tpv3CtrlCfgPWCap.description: The pseudowire capabilities of this control connection entry. Each octet must be a value within the range specified by the L2tpv3PWType textual convention.

l2tpv3CtrlCfgFallback.name: l2tpv3CtrlCfgFallback
l2tpv3CtrlCfgFallback.description: Indicates whether fallback to older versions of L2TP is enabled during control connection establishment.

l2tpv3CtrlCfgDrain.name: l2tpv3CtrlCfgDrain
l2tpv3CtrlCfgDrain.description: Setting this object to 'true' prevents any new sessions from being either initiated or accepted by this control connection. However, it does not disconnect any active sessions for this control connection. The 'l2tpv3CtrlStatsIsDraining' object for this control connection is set to 'true'. To cancel a drain, this object is set to 'false'. This object may be overridden by the global 'l2tpv3StackCfgDrain' object, which globally applies drain settings to all control connections.

l2tpv3CtrlCfgAuth.name: l2tpv3CtrlCfgAuth
l2tpv3CtrlCfgAuth.description: Describes how a pair of LCCEs are to be authenticated. The value 'simple' indicates that peers are authenticated by their host name as described in the Host Name AVP. The value 'challenge' indicates that all peers are challenged to prove their identification. This object cannot be modified when the control connection is in a connecting or connected state.

l2tpv3CtrlCfgSecret.name: l2tpv3CtrlCfgSecret
l2tpv3CtrlCfgSecret.description: The shared secret used during the authentication phase of control connection establishment. This object cannot be modified when the control connection is in a connecting or connected state. This object MUST be accessible only via requests using both authentication and privacy. The agent MUST report an empty string in response to get, get-next, and get-bulk requests.

l2tpv3CtrlCfgSecurity.name: l2tpv3CtrlCfgSecurity
l2tpv3CtrlCfgSecurity.description: Sets whether this control connection is to be secured. The value of 'ipsec' indicates that all control packets have IPsec headers. The types of IPsec headers (e.g. AH, ESP, etc.) and their usage are outside the scope of this document. This object cannot be modified when the control connection is in a connecting or connected state.

l2tpv3CtrlCfgHelloInt.name: l2tpv3CtrlCfgHelloInt
l2tpv3CtrlCfgHelloInt.description: The interval in which Hello (keepalive) packets are sent by a local peer. The value zero effectively disables the sending of Hello packets. Modifications to this object have immediate effect.

l2tpv3CtrlCfgRWS.name: l2tpv3CtrlCfgRWS
l2tpv3CtrlCfgRWS.description: The control packet receive window size. It specifies the maximum number of control packets an LCCE can send for the control connection without waiting for an acknowledgement from the peer. This object cannot be modified when the control connection is in a connecting or connected state.

l2tpv3CtrlCfgMaxRetrans.name: l2tpv3CtrlCfgMaxRetrans
l2tpv3CtrlCfgMaxRetrans.description: The number of control packet retransmissions that the L2TP stack attempts for this control connection before assuming that the peer is no longer responding. A value of zero indicates that this peer does not attempt to retransmit an unacknowledged control packet. Modifications to this object have immediate effect.

l2tpv3CtrlCfgMaxRetransTO.name: l2tpv3CtrlCfgMaxRetransTO
l2tpv3CtrlCfgMaxRetransTO.description: The maximum retransmission timeout interval that the control connection waits before retransmitting an unacknowledged control packet. Modifications to this object have immediate effect.

l2tpv3CtrlCfgReassemblyTO.name: l2tpv3CtrlCfgReassemblyTO
l2tpv3CtrlCfgReassemblyTO.description: The number of milliseconds that this control connection waits before processing data packets that were received out of sequence (and that are being held for processing in sequence). A low value increases the chance of delayed packets being discarded, while a high value may cause more queueing and possibly degrade throughput if packets are truly lost. The default value for this object is zero, which means that delayed packets are considered lost, and received packets are processed in increasing order, despite any sequence number gaps.

l2tpv3CtrlCfgIdleTO.name: l2tpv3CtrlCfgIdleTO
l2tpv3CtrlCfgIdleTO.description: The period of time that an established control connection with no sessions waits before disconnecting the control connection. A value of zero indicates that the control connection disconnects immediately after the last session disconnects. A value of -1 leaves the control connection up indefinitely. Modifications to this object have immediate effect.

l2tpv3CtrlStatsTable.name: l2tpv3CtrlStatsTable
l2tpv3CtrlStatsTable.description: Table describing the current status and statistics of a single L2TP control connection. There is a 1:1 correspondence between conceptual rows of this table and conceptual rows of the l2tpv3CtrlCfgTable.

l2tpv3CtrlStatsEntry.name: l2tpv3CtrlStatsEntry
l2tpv3CtrlStatsEntry.description: An L2TP control connection interface statistics entry.

l2tpv3CtrlStatsRemoteRouterID.name: l2tpv3CtrlStatsRemoteRouterID
l2tpv3CtrlStatsRemoteRouterID.description: The remote router ID for this control connection, as communicated by the peer via the Router ID AVP.

l2tpv3CtrlStatsState.name: l2tpv3CtrlStatsState
l2tpv3CtrlStatsState.description: The current state of the control connection.

l2tpv3CtrlStatsIsDraining.name: l2tpv3CtrlStatsIsDraining
l2tpv3CtrlStatsIsDraining.description: Indicates whether the control connection is draining sessions. This object is set to 'true' if either 'l2tpv3StackCfgDrain' or 'l2tpv3CtrlCfgDrain' is set to 'true', and is only set to 'false' if both configuration objects are 'false'.

l2tpv3CtrlStatsInitiated.name: l2tpv3CtrlStatsInitiated
l2tpv3CtrlStatsInitiated.description: Indicates whether the control connection was initiated locally or remotely.

l2tpv3CtrlStatsRemoteHostName.name: l2tpv3CtrlStatsRemoteHostName
l2tpv3CtrlStatsRemoteHostName.description: The peer's host name as discovered during the control connection establishment (via the Host Name AVP). If the control connection is idle, this object should maintain its value from the last time it was connected.

l2tpv3CtrlStatsRemoteVendorName.name: l2tpv3CtrlStatsRemoteVendorName
l2tpv3CtrlStatsRemoteVendorName.description: The vendor name of the peer. If the control connection is idle, this object should maintain its value from the last time it was connected.

l2tpv3CtrlStatsRemotePWCap.name: l2tpv3CtrlStatsRemotePWCap
l2tpv3CtrlStatsRemotePWCap.description: The peer's pseudowire capabilities for this control connection. Each octet must be a value within the range specified by the L2tpv3PWType textual convention.

l2tpv3CtrlStatsRemoteVersion.name: l2tpv3CtrlStatsRemoteVersion
l2tpv3CtrlStatsRemoteVersion.description: The peer implementation's protocol version number and revision number. The first octet contains the protocol version number. The second octet contains the protocol revision number.

l2tpv3CtrlStatsInitialRemoteRWS.name: l2tpv3CtrlStatsInitialRemoteRWS
l2tpv3CtrlStatsInitialRemoteRWS.description: The peer's receive window size as conveyed during control connection establishment (via the Remote Window Size AVP). If the control connection is idle, this object should maintain its value from the last time it was connected.

l2tpv3CtrlStatsCtrlRxZLB.name: l2tpv3CtrlStatsCtrlRxZLB
l2tpv3CtrlStatsCtrlRxZLB.description: The number of Zero-Length-Body (acknowledgement) control packets that have been received on the control connection.

l2tpv3CtrlStatsCtrlOutOfSeq.name: l2tpv3CtrlStatsCtrlOutOfSeq
l2tpv3CtrlStatsCtrlOutOfSeq.description: The number of control packets that have been received out of order (per the sequence numbers) on this control connection, including out of window packets.

l2tpv3CtrlStatsCtrlOutOfWindow.name: l2tpv3CtrlStatsCtrlOutOfWindow
l2tpv3CtrlStatsCtrlOutOfWindow.description: The number of control packets that have been received outside of the offered receive window for the control connection. Whether these packets are queued or discarded is implementation-specific.

l2tpv3CtrlStatsCtrlTxZLB.name: l2tpv3CtrlStatsCtrlTxZLB
l2tpv3CtrlStatsCtrlTxZLB.description: The number of Zero-Length-Body (acknowledgement) control packets that have been sent to the peer for this control connection.

l2tpv3CtrlStatsCtrlAckTO.name: l2tpv3CtrlStatsCtrlAckTO
l2tpv3CtrlStatsCtrlAckTO.description: The number of control packet timeouts due to late acknowledgements from the peer for this control connection.

l2tpv3CtrlStatsCurrentRemoteRWS.name: l2tpv3CtrlStatsCurrentRemoteRWS
l2tpv3CtrlStatsCurrentRemoteRWS.description: The current remote receive window size as determined by the local flow control mechanism employed.

l2tpv3CtrlStatsTxSeq.name: l2tpv3CtrlStatsTxSeq
l2tpv3CtrlStatsTxSeq.description: The next send (Ns) sequence number for the control connection.

l2tpv3CtrlStatsRxSeq.name: l2tpv3CtrlStatsRxSeq
l2tpv3CtrlStatsRxSeq.description: The next receive (Nr) sequence number for the control connection.

l2tpv3CtrlStatsNumSessCumEst.name: l2tpv3CtrlStatsNumSessCumEst
l2tpv3CtrlStatsNumSessCumEst.description: The cumulative number of sessions that this control connection has established during its lifetime.

l2tpv3CtrlStatsNumSessCurrentEst.name: l2tpv3CtrlStatsNumSessCurrentEst
l2tpv3CtrlStatsNumSessCurrentEst.description: The number of sessions currently in the established state for this control connection.

l2tpv3CtrlStatsNumSessFailed.name: l2tpv3CtrlStatsNumSessFailed
l2tpv3CtrlStatsNumSessFailed.description: The total number of sessions that were negotiated but failed to be established by this control connection.

l2tpv3CtrlStatsLastResultCode.name: l2tpv3CtrlStatsLastResultCode
l2tpv3CtrlStatsLastResultCode.description: The result code as conveyed by the Result Code AVP from the most recent session to be torn down.

l2tpv3CtrlStatsLastErrorCode.name: l2tpv3CtrlStatsLastErrorCode
l2tpv3CtrlStatsLastErrorCode.description: The error code as conveyed by the Result Code AVP from the most recent session to be torn down.

l2tpv3CtrlStatsLastErrorMessage.name: l2tpv3CtrlStatsLastErrorMessage
l2tpv3CtrlStatsLastErrorMessage.description: The optional message as conveyed by the Result Code AVP from the most recent session to be torn down.

l2tpv3CtrlStatsCtrlRxOctets.name: l2tpv3CtrlStatsCtrlRxOctets
l2tpv3CtrlStatsCtrlRxOctets.description: The number of control octets that have been received by this control connection.

l2tpv3CtrlStatsCtrlRxPkts.name: l2tpv3CtrlStatsCtrlRxPkts
l2tpv3CtrlStatsCtrlRxPkts.description: The number of control packets that have been received by this control connection.

l2tpv3CtrlStatsCtrlTxOctets.name: l2tpv3CtrlStatsCtrlTxOctets
l2tpv3CtrlStatsCtrlTxOctets.description: The number of control octets that have been sent by this control connection.

l2tpv3CtrlStatsCtrlTxPkts.name: l2tpv3CtrlStatsCtrlTxPkts
l2tpv3CtrlStatsCtrlTxPkts.description: The number of control packets that have been sent by this control connection.

l2tpv3CtrlStatsDataRxOctets.name: l2tpv3CtrlStatsDataRxOctets
l2tpv3CtrlStatsDataRxOctets.description: The number of data octets that have been received by sessions negotiated by this control connection.

l2tpv3CtrlStatsDataRxPkts.name: l2tpv3CtrlStatsDataRxPkts
l2tpv3CtrlStatsDataRxPkts.description: The number of data packets that have been received by sessions negotiated by this control connection.

l2tpv3CtrlStatsDataRxDrops.name: l2tpv3CtrlStatsDataRxDrops
l2tpv3CtrlStatsDataRxDrops.description: The number of received data packets that have been dropped by sessions negotiated by this control connection.

l2tpv3CtrlStatsDataTxOctets.name: l2tpv3CtrlStatsDataTxOctets
l2tpv3CtrlStatsDataTxOctets.description: The number of data octets that have been sent by sessions negotiated by this control connection.

l2tpv3CtrlStatsDataTxPkts.name: l2tpv3CtrlStatsDataTxPkts
l2tpv3CtrlStatsDataTxPkts.description: The number of data packets that have been sent by sessions negotiated by this control connection.

l2tpv3CtrlMapTable.name: l2tpv3CtrlMapTable
l2tpv3CtrlMapTable.description: Table intended to assist management applications to quickly determine the ifIndex value for a given local control connection ID.

l2tpv3CtrlMapEntry.name: l2tpv3CtrlMapEntry
l2tpv3CtrlMapEntry.description: An L2TP control connection index map entry.

l2tpv3CtrlMapIfIndex.name: l2tpv3CtrlMapIfIndex
l2tpv3CtrlMapIfIndex.description: The ifIndex value of a control connection interface, represented in the Interfaces Group MIB as an entry with an interface type of L2TP.

l2tpv3SessionCfgTable.name: l2tpv3SessionCfgTable
l2tpv3SessionCfgTable.description: Table used to (re)configure the operational characteristics of a single L2TP session. There is a 1:1 correspondence between conceptual rows of this table and conceptual rows of the l2tpv3SessionStatsTable. Entries in this table have the same persistency characteristics as that of the l2tpv3SessionStatsTable.

l2tpv3SessionCfgEntry.name: l2tpv3SessionCfgEntry
l2tpv3SessionCfgEntry.description: An L2TP session configuration entry. Entries in this table are added and deleted as a result of protocol interactions or management operations.

l2tpv3SessionCfgIfIndex.name: l2tpv3SessionCfgIfIndex
l2tpv3SessionCfgIfIndex.description: The ifIndex value of the interface from which L2 frames are being forwarded. For example, the ifIndex could be a DS0 on an LAC or a virtual PPP interface on an LNS.

l2tpv3SessionCfgCtrlLocalID.name: l2tpv3SessionCfgCtrlLocalID
l2tpv3SessionCfgCtrlLocalID.description: Sets the local control connection ID of the control connection with which this session may be associated. If the session is not associated with a control connection, the value of this object is 0.

l2tpv3SessionCfgPWType.name: l2tpv3SessionCfgPWType
l2tpv3SessionCfgPWType.description: Sets the pseudowire type of the session, which is sent to the peer via the Pseudowire Type AVP.

l2tpv3SessionCfgEndID.name: l2tpv3SessionCfgEndID
l2tpv3SessionCfgEndID.description: Sets the End Identifier that is sent to the peer via the End ID AVP.

l2tpv3SessionCfgAppID.name: l2tpv3SessionCfgAppID
l2tpv3SessionCfgAppID.description: Sets the Application Code and Application Info that are sent to the peer via the Application ID AVP.

l2tpv3SessionCfgPWEncap.name: l2tpv3SessionCfgPWEncap
l2tpv3SessionCfgPWEncap.description: Sets the Control Encapsulation Type that is sent to the peer via the Pseudowire Control Encapsulation AVP.

l2tpv3SessionCfgSeq.name: l2tpv3SessionCfgSeq
l2tpv3SessionCfgSeq.description: Sets the Data Sequencing Level that is required of the peer. Sent to the peer via the Data Sequencing AVP.

l2tpv3SessionCfgLocalCookie.name: l2tpv3SessionCfgLocalCookie
l2tpv3SessionCfgLocalCookie.description: Sets the local cookie that is included in outgoing data packets.

l2tpv3SessionCfgRemoteCookie.name: l2tpv3SessionCfgRemoteCookie
l2tpv3SessionCfgRemoteCookie.description: Sets the remote cookie that is expected in incoming data packets.

l2tpv3SessionCfgCallType.name: l2tpv3SessionCfgCallType
l2tpv3SessionCfgCallType.description: The role this LCCE is playing for this session. For example, 'lacInitiator' indicates that this control connection peer is acting as an LAC and generated an call request (ICRQ or OCRQ) to its peer.

l2tpv3SessionStatsTable.name: l2tpv3SessionStatsTable
l2tpv3SessionStatsTable.description: Table that describes the current status and statistics of a single L2TP session.

l2tpv3SessionStatsEntry.name: l2tpv3SessionStatsEntry
l2tpv3SessionStatsEntry.description: An L2TP session interface statistics entry.

l2tpv3SessionStatsRemoteEndID.name: l2tpv3SessionStatsRemoteEndID
l2tpv3SessionStatsRemoteEndID.description: The peer's End Identifier, as communicated via the End ID AVP.

l2tpv3SessionStatsRemoteAppID.name: l2tpv3SessionStatsRemoteAppID
l2tpv3SessionStatsRemoteAppID.description: The peer's Application Code and Application Info, as communicated via the Application ID AVP.

l2tpv3SessionStatsRemotePWEncap.name: l2tpv3SessionStatsRemotePWEncap
l2tpv3SessionStatsRemotePWEncap.description: The peer's Control Encapsulation Type, as communicated via the Pseudowire Control Encapsulation AVP.

l2tpv3SessionStatsRemoteSeq.name: l2tpv3SessionStatsRemoteSeq
l2tpv3SessionStatsRemoteSeq.description: The peer's Data Sequencing Level, as communicated via the Data Sequencing AVP.

l2tpv3SessionStatsState.name: l2tpv3SessionStatsState
l2tpv3SessionStatsState.description: The current state of the session.

l2tpv3SessionStatsCircuitStatus.name: l2tpv3SessionStatsCircuitStatus
l2tpv3SessionStatsCircuitStatus.description: The current status of the circuit forwarded by the session.

l2tpv3SessionStatsSerialNumber.name: l2tpv3SessionStatsSerialNumber
l2tpv3SessionStatsSerialNumber.description: The serial number that has been assigned to this session.

l2tpv3SessionStatsRxConnectSpeed.name: l2tpv3SessionStatsRxConnectSpeed
l2tpv3SessionStatsRxConnectSpeed.description: The last known receive baud rate for this session.

l2tpv3SessionStatsTxConnectSpeed.name: l2tpv3SessionStatsTxConnectSpeed
l2tpv3SessionStatsTxConnectSpeed.description: The last known transmit baud rate for this session.

l2tpv3SessionStatsPhysChannelID.name: l2tpv3SessionStatsPhysChannelID
l2tpv3SessionStatsPhysChannelID.description: The physical channel identifier for the session.

l2tpv3SessionStatsPrivateGroupID.name: l2tpv3SessionStatsPrivateGroupID
l2tpv3SessionStatsPrivateGroupID.description: The private group ID used for this L2TP session. If no private group ID is found, then a null string is returned.

l2tpv3SessionStatsOutOfSeq.name: l2tpv3SessionStatsOutOfSeq
l2tpv3SessionStatsOutOfSeq.description: The total number of data packets received out of sequence for this session.

l2tpv3SessionStatsReassemblyTO.name: l2tpv3SessionStatsReassemblyTO
l2tpv3SessionStatsReassemblyTO.description: The number of reassembly timeouts that have occurred for this session.

l2tpv3SessionStatsTxSeq.name: l2tpv3SessionStatsTxSeq
l2tpv3SessionStatsTxSeq.description: The current sequence number for outgoing data packets for this session.

l2tpv3SessionStatsRxSeq.name: l2tpv3SessionStatsRxSeq
l2tpv3SessionStatsRxSeq.description: The current sequence number for incoming data packets for this session.

l2tpv3SessionStatsRxOctets.name: l2tpv3SessionStatsRxOctets
l2tpv3SessionStatsRxOctets.description: The number of data octets that have been received by this session.

l2tpv3SessionStatsRxPkts.name: l2tpv3SessionStatsRxPkts
l2tpv3SessionStatsRxPkts.description: The number of data packets that have been received by this session.

l2tpv3SessionStatsRxDrops.name: l2tpv3SessionStatsRxDrops
l2tpv3SessionStatsRxDrops.description: The number of received data packets that have been dropped by this session.

l2tpv3SessionStatsTxOctets.name: l2tpv3SessionStatsTxOctets
l2tpv3SessionStatsTxOctets.description: The number of data octets that have been sent by this session.

l2tpv3SessionStatsTxPkts.name: l2tpv3SessionStatsTxPkts
l2tpv3SessionStatsTxPkts.description: The number of data packets that have been sent by this session.

l2tpv3SessionMapTable.name: l2tpv3SessionMapTable
l2tpv3SessionMapTable.description: Table intended to assist management applications to map interfaces to control connection and session IDs.

l2tpv3SessionMapEntry.name: l2tpv3SessionMapEntry
l2tpv3SessionMapEntry.description: An L2TP session index map entry.

l2tpv3SessionMapIfIndex.name: l2tpv3SessionMapIfIndex
l2tpv3SessionMapIfIndex.description: The ifIndex value of the interface being forwarded via an L2TP session. For example, the interface could be an Ethernet interface on an LAC or a virtual PPP interface on the LNS.

l2tpv3SessionMapCtrlIfIndex.name: l2tpv3SessionMapCtrlIfIndex
l2tpv3SessionMapCtrlIfIndex.description: The ifIndex value of the session's control connection. The object establishes a binding between a particular interface identified by l2tpv3SessionMapIfIndex to a particular control connection.

l2tpv3SessionMapLocalID.name: l2tpv3SessionMapLocalID
l2tpv3SessionMapLocalID.description: The local session ID for this session.

l2tpv3SessionMapStatus.name: l2tpv3SessionMapStatus
l2tpv3SessionMapStatus.description: The status of this session map entry.

l2tpv3CtrlAuthFailure.name: l2tpv3CtrlAuthFailure
l2tpv3CtrlAuthFailure.description: Trap signifying that an attempt to establish a control connection to a remote peer has failed authentication.

l2tpv3MIBFullCompliance.name: l2tpv3MIBFullCompliance
l2tpv3MIBFullCompliance.description: An implementation claims full compliance when this MIB is implemented with support for read-create and read- write operations, thereby allowing configuration and monitoring, respectively.

l2tpv3MIBReadOnlyCompliance.name: l2tpv3MIBReadOnlyCompliance
l2tpv3MIBReadOnlyCompliance.description: An implementation claims read-only compliance when this MIB is implemented without support for read-create and read-write operations (i.e. operates in read-only mode), thereby allowing monitoring but not configuration.

l2tpv3CfgGroup.name: l2tpv3CfgGroup
l2tpv3CfgGroup.description: A collection of objects providing configuration information of the L2TP stack, its control connections, and its sessions.

l2tpv3StatsGroup.name: l2tpv3StatsGroup
l2tpv3StatsGroup.description: A collection of objects providing status and statistics of the L2TP stack, its control connections, and its sessions.

l2tpv3MappingGroup.name: l2tpv3MappingGroup
l2tpv3MappingGroup.description: A collection of objects providing index mapping.

l2tpv3SecurityGroup.name: l2tpv3SecurityGroup
l2tpv3SecurityGroup.description: A collection of objects providing L2TP security configuration.

l2tpv3TrapGroup.name: l2tpv3TrapGroup
l2tpv3TrapGroup.description: A collection of L2TP trap events as specified in NOTIFICATION-TYPE constructs.

l2tpv3HCPacketGroup.name: l2tpv3HCPacketGroup
l2tpv3HCPacketGroup.description: A collection of objects providing high-capacity 64-bit counter objects.
